Strategic Advantages
Regional Access and Proximity to Houston Staples

Huge Tax Savings

Workforce Training

Since 2000, the population of Pearland, Texas, a suburb of Houston located about 15 miles south of Downtown Houston, has essentially quadrupled to more than 114,000 residents. Moreover, the city consistently ranks among the safest in the Lone Star State. ,From a warehouse and distribution perspective, it has direct access to State Highway 288, Texas State Highway 35, and Sam Houston Tollway that can connect distributors with the growing population in this part of Houston. As suburban south Houston continues to grow, so should industrial demand for e-commerce and distribution uses in the future. ,A notable amount of wholesale trade tenants serving the oil and gas industry are located here. Some of the area's largest industrial tenants include Texas Steel Conversion, Inc. (500,000 square feet), O'Reilly Auto Parts (490,000 square feet), Powell Industries, Inc. (430,000 square feet), RTI Fabrications, L.P. (310,000 square feet), and National Oilwell Varco (300,000 square feet).,Asking rents are noticeably below the metro average, offering an attractive discount to tenants.
propOverview: Located just 5 blocks south of Loop 610, 5400 Cedar Crest Way offers businesses a unique opportunity with more than 40,000 square feet of warehouse and office space that has seen updated electrical service, lighting, and building exteriors. Between 10 different structures on the property, industrial users have access to climate-controlled warehouses, portable office buildings, storage facilities, cranes, and high power options. The four major buildings on the property are Buildings A, B, C, and D. Building A is the main building, with a 20’ eave height, 2 (two) 45’ wide bays, 2 (two) 5-ton bridge cranes, and 480/277 volt electrical service with transformers and breaker panels strategically placed throughout the building. 7,000 square feet of the warehouse is climate controlled, and there are 4 (four) overhead doors. Buildings B and C are currently configured as machines shops, each featuring up to 480-volt power options,  2 (two) overhead doors, and climate-controlled industrial space. Building C also features a 5-ton bridge crane system that is 30’ wide and 58’ in length. Building D is the last property featuring 480-volt power service, and also offers 2 (two) overhead doors and 12’ eave heights. Buildings E- J offer office and storage space, with many of the buildings being Morgan Portable Buildings that can be moved around the site based on business needs. The expansive site features perimeter chain link fencing, a fully paved lot, and the current configuration of the buildings offers an adequate turn radius for 18-wheelers. This prime location sits just minutes from Loop 610, 2.15 miles west of the Gulf Freeway/IH45, and 5 miles southeast of the Houston Central Business District for easy transportation. Additionally, the William P Hobby Airport is accessible in a 15-minute drive and the Port of Houston can be reached in 11 minutes. This central location also offers easy access to food, shopping, and daily conveniences options for employees. The building is surrounded by dense residential areas, providing a robust labor pool that will enjoy the short commutes to and from work.

propOverview: Situated on a 7.3-acre business park in the desirable Near Northwest submarket, 6507 West Little York Road offers amenities and conveniences to meet the needs of today’s industrial tenants. The Northwest Place Industrial Park features five attractive, tilt-wall facilities and a fully curbed and nicely landscaped access road that connects Bingle and West Little York Roads. 6507 West Little York boasts a rare drive-thru opportunity with 2 (two) 12’x12’ and 2 (two) 16’x16’ grade-level, over-sized roll-up doors. The building also offers the capability for a 10-ton crane, and there is currently a high-pile permit in place for storage. Other features include divisibility down to 9,000 square feet, 3,737 square feet of office space, a 24’ eave height, two warehouse exhaust fans, T-5 high-bay fluorescent light fixtures throughout the warehouse, 480volt, 3-phase, 400 amp power, exterior wall pack lighting, and a controlled-mode ELO sprinkler system in place. The site offers ample outside storage and employee parking options, and from the connecting road commuters, customers and cargo alike enjoy easy access to the nearby major highways. Both I-45 and I-10 are reached in 15 minutes or less, and from there, three major airports can be reached in an hour drive or less. The Houston George Bush Intercontinental Airport is 26 minutes from the site, the William P Hobby Airport is 41, and the Ellington Field Airport is 54. It is also only a 30-minute drive to the Port of Houston and an 8-minute drive to the Tencon Industries, Inc rail line. The Near Northwest industrial submarket has experienced low vacancy rates and strong demand for space over the past few years. With no reported industrial space under construction as of the end of 2019, 6507 West Little York Road offers an excellent opportunity for tenants to locate their business in this area.

highlights: Brand new, master-planned industrial project in a prime North Houston location.,Major infrastructure improvements to the park including regional detention and extensive road expansion.,Located immediately south of IAH Airport with direct access to domestic and international air freight.,State-of-the-art distribution facility with front load configuration, 32' clear height, and ample trailer stalls.,Ideal distribution location immediately off of Beltway 8 and within 5 miles to major regional thoroughfares including I-45, US 59 and Hardy Toll Rd.
hoodMarket: The North Hardy Toll Road’s location between the heavily trafficked Interstate 10 and Beltway 8, as well as its proximity to the George Bush Intercontinental Airport, makes it well positioned to satisfy demand generated by the nearby population growth. ,Since 2010, more than 80% of Harris County's population growth has occurred in its unincorporated areas. The majority immediately to the west and increasingly the east of the submarket, especially with the completion of the Grand Parkway. The North Hardy Toll Road also benefits from rooftop growth in Montgomery County to the north, particularly Springwoods Village, The Woodlands, and Conroe. The area draws distribution tenants looking to be close to the fastest-growing population region in Houston and in a newer stock of buildings. ,The area’s industrial inventory has grown by nearly 50% since 2010. Yet vacancies remain relatively low. Among the largest recent developments, Grocers Supply and Conn’s HomePlus moved into their build-to-suits in the area recently. And DB Schenker moved into its new distribution location nearby. Distribution tenants tend to prefer buildings with higher clear heights, stronger load bearing walls, and larger truck bays.,Rents in the North Hardy Toll area are below neighboring areas, particularly to the north and west.
propOverview: Presidents Park is Houston's newest and most flexible master-planned industrial project.  The first installment, Presidents Park 5, is currently under construction and is expected to be completed in Q2 2020.  This speculative building can suit either single or multi-tenant needs with glass storefront entrances on both ends and ample auto and trailer parking.  The state-of-the-art, front-load space will have 32' clear height, a modern 185' truck court, LED interior and exterior lights, and ESFR sprinklers.  The park itself is undergoing major infrastructure improvements including upgrading and expanding Milner Road for easier and quicker access in and out of the park. Presidents Park’s strategic location in north Houston, immediately south of IAH Airport, provides unmatched access to the ever-growing Houston MSA population and business centers. The park is located less than 5 miles from all three major north/south arteries, including I-45, Hardy Toll Road and Hwy 59, and boasts immediate access to Beltway 8 and a 10-minute drive to the 610 Loop for excellent circulation around the city of Houston. This key location combined with Presidents Park’s best-in-class design and state-of-the-art facilities creates an ideal setting for future growth.

propOverview:
This is a clean well cared for street to street industrial building in the heart of East Williamsburg Brooklyn. Conveniently located close with a short 4 block walk to the "L" train  and in close proximity to the BQE and the Williamsburg Bridge. The building's neighborhood is an artistic community and is filled with interesting shops, restaurants, entertainment venues, galleries and work shops who live in harmony with the remaining industrial users . There are separate entrances to warehouse/shop and for the office/showroom which are beautifully appointed with wood floors, barn doors and plenty of light with a  modern and rustic industrial feel. Their are two units available that are interconnected and can be take together or separately.Unit #1 is approximately 7,000nSF and goes street to street, it has beautiful office space divided into private offices as well as a large open office perfect for work sharing or showroom. Unit #2 is approximately 3,000 SF with an opened  well lit open work area as well as a private office and a room built out for photography and filming. Both units have multiple bathrooms, high ceilings, direct street access, great light, are fully sprinkled and have street level loading. Perfect for any warehouse use, photography, artist studio, gallery, fabrication, wood shop, or any other industrial use. We are asking $26/sf/year and will entertain offers. To make arrangements to see the spaces or if you have any questions please feel to call Jean at 917-586-1814 there is NO BROKERAGE FEE for tenant. 
Come take a look and bring your imagination. Wonderful, clean, well cared for building in a exciting East Williamsburg. Close to all the community has to offer.

hoodMarket: Miami Airport East is a primarily industrial area located in the center of the Miami region, home to Miami International Airport (MIA). The area borders Southwest Eighth Street to the south, Palmetto Expressway to the west, East Okeechobee Road to the north, and Northwest 42nd Avenue to the east. Dolphin Expressway cuts through the center of the area. The bulk of properties are clustered around the west side of MIA and across Palmetto Expressway, at the Norfolk Southern intermodal terminal on Northwest 69th Avenue, providing access to rail. ,Proximity to MIA and access to major Florida highway arteries and freight train lines have been drawing tenants to this industrial area. Industries with a significant presence in the area include transportation and logistics, food and beverage wholesalers, flower importers, and some manufacturing. The area’s largest tenants are CEVA Logistics, Floral Logistics of Miami, and Amazon. ,Demand for industrial space has consistently grown as Miami’s economy and international trade have boomed over the past decade. Developable land around MIA has become increasingly scarce after significant industrial development earlier in the economic expansion; several parts have been rezoned, and apartment developers have moved in. The lack of new industrial space has led to higher rents.
propOverview:
Located adjacent to the Miami International Airport with unparalleled access to South Florida’s busiest air and sea ports, the South Florida Logistics Center
is a unique 200-acre logistics complex that serves as a true inter-modal transfer point for goods moving through South Florida by all modes of 
transportation—railroad, highway, ocean, and air. Building 1 is located just North of NW 36th Street, and offers easy access to the MIA cargo entrance.

The area’s largest tenants are CEVA Logistics, Floral Logistics of Miami, and Amazon. ,Demand for industrial space has consistently grown as Miami’s economy and international trade have boomed over the past decade. Developable land around MIA has become increasingly scarce after significant industrial development earlier in the economic expansion; several parts have been rezoned, and apartment developers have moved in. The lack of new industrial space has led to higher rents.
propOverview: Located adjacent to the Miami International Airport with unparalleled access to South Florida’s busiest air and sea ports, the South Florida Logistics Center is a unique 200-acre logistics complex that serves as a true intermodal transfer point for goods moving through South Florida by all modes of transportation—railroad, highway, ocean, and air. Building 8 is located just South of NW 36th Street, and offers easy access to the MIA cargo entrance.

highlights: Matrix Global Logistics Park – Staten Island is a master-planned distribution park with tenants like Amazon and IKEA already in place.,Cross-docked distribution facility that is available for a build-to-suit and will include a 40’ clear height and ample trailer and car parking.,25-year tax abatements to less than 1/3 of comparable New Jersey locations and an abundant labor force for all employee ranks.,Immediate access to Staten Island Expressway and Route 440, opening up access to New Jersey Turnpike and Brooklyn-Queens Expressway in minutes.,Connected to an excellent distribution network with efficient inbound access to New Jersey Ports and contiguous to the New York Container Terminal.
hoodMarket: Staten Island is the southernmost borough of New York City, connecting to Brooklyn with the Verrazano Bridge. The island is also connected to New Jersey, with easy access to the New Jersey Turnpike. Direct transit to Manhattan is limited to the Staten Island Ferry, however. It is the least populated of the five boroughs and with a distinctly suburban atmosphere, compared to the rest of New York City.,Amazon is the largest occupier in Staten Island, with more than 1.5 million square feet of distribution space. The area has benefitted from the continued growth of e-commerce and expansion of ‘last-mile’ distribution hubs. IKEA is also a dominant presence, with nearly 1 million square feet of space. The tenant mix is otherwise a mix of logistics, retail and restaurant supplier occupiers.,Construction in Staten Island has been muted, other than in 2018 when 1.8 million square feet delivered. New warehouse facilities are in demand, as IKEA and Amazon have taken much of what is available.
propOverview: Matrix Global Logistics Park – Staten Island is in an ideal location within a master-planned distribution park. The park currently boasts facilities for Amazon and IKEA, with more construction planned. This site has the potential for a 975,000 square-foot distribution facility available on a build-to-suit basis. The building will utilize industry-leading design features, 40’ clear heights, a cross-docked layout, and ample overhead doors, trailer parking, and car parking to meet business needs. The location on Staten Island offers efficient access to Manhattan, Brooklyn, Queens, and Long Island with immediate access to Staten Island Expressway and Route 440, which connect with New Jersey Turnpike or Brooklyn-Queens Expressway in minutes. These major highways allow access to roughly one-third of the nation’s population within a day’s drive. For inbound/outbound shipping, the New Jersey Ports are within a half-hour drive, and the site is contiguous to the New York Container Terminal on Staten Island. The surrounding area provides an excellent labor force for all ranks of employees, with 157,024 residents in a 3-mile radius.

The building carries a City of Burbank mailing address but is physically located in Sun Valley (The City of Los Angeles).

spaceSummary: 20310 Plummer Street is a best-in-class, corporate headquarters/distribution facility located in the heart of Chatsworth. spaceSummary: The previous tenant ran a bakery operation at this food processing unit.  There are a number of costly structural improvements such as floor drains, tiled walls, drop ceiling, ADA-compliant facility features, and kitchen-tailored electrical, plumbing, and gas line hookups.    You still need to re-coat the floor with a code-compliant paint and install all of your required commercial appliances for your business.  There is still a large rectangular-like opening in the drop ceiling because the previous tenant had a large appliance that exceeded the height of the drop ceiling.  If you install a tall refrigerator for instance in the same area, to close the ceiling hole, all you would need to do is add a few more ceiling tiles until it is flush with your new appliance.

highlights: Located minutes from highway 60,  I-605 and I-10,Prices vary dependant on square footage and length of term.,On-Site Office with Warehouse
propOverview:
This spacious industrial rental nestled in between Hacienda Heights and West Covina is brought to you by CubeWork. The 112,000 SF workspace is available in flexible full service gross lease terms starting at 200 SF. First constructed in 1972, the 112,000 SF building has received numerous sleek and modern upgrades as of late. Located just minutes from Highway 60, I-605, and I-10, this rental location is a perfect option for any company who genuinely considers their employees’ commutes.
Often referred to as “Industry” by the locals, this area is home to over 3,000 businesses and 67,000 jobs and only a 20 minute commute from downtown Los Angeles. Of these businesses, 92% are dedicated to industrial, and the other 8% commercial. A popular choice for tech related companies, the surrounding areas of Rowland Heights, Hacienda Heights, West Covina, Diamond Bar, and Walnut are ideal options in terms of working with the lovely surrounding mountains as your backdrop. The City of Industry has an average yearly temperature of 77 degrees and the sun shines down upon the city over 250 days a year, making it an excellent choice to call home for your business. 
About Cubework Facilities:
Cubework offers standard and custom commercial warehouse space available for immediate use. With unmatched flexibility, our 300 to 20,000 square foot spaces are suitable for general warehousing to production and light manufacturing. All warehouse spaces can be built-to-suit your needs and we have experienced professionals who will work with you to ensure that your space matches your business needs. 
Our facilities offer spanning warehouses with office buildings, as well as beautifully designed lounges, conference rooms, and private offices. Commuting is a breeze; we are located only minutes away from freeways and have convenient parking spots once you’ve arrived. We have at each Cubework location on-site staff from front desk-service to personal support for you throughout the workweek. Our cleaning crew helps around the clock keeping common areas, meeting rooms, and private offices looking their spiffiest. Dedicated meeting spaces include A/V gear and details like custom artwork. Hook yourself up to hard-wired Ethernet or secure Wi-Fi; with IT support and guest log-in functionality included. Our unique common areas are living room styled spaces designed for creativity, comfort and productivity. 
Cubework is the fastest growing industrial work space in the US adding a new location every 10 days! The company has over 30 locations with 4 million square feet of modern industrial coworking space in 25 cities. For an inviting warehouse and office coworking experience that puts you in the center of the action, schedule a visit today!

propOverview: One-story multi-use creative building located at the northeast signalized corner of 7th Street and Rio Street. The property is situated just east of the DTLA Arts District, and is just minutes from numerous new retail, restaurant, office, hotel and residential properties. The offering is highly secure, and provides a user with a perfect opportunity to create a private club or bar, studio, gallery, professional or creative offices, etc. The building was completely remodeled in 2019 and is available for immediate possession. One-half mile east of Santa Fe Avenue. Just blocks from 300,000 SF creative campus at 7th and Anderson Streets. Nearby neighbors include new Warner Chappell Music building, Firehouse Hotel, Bread Lounge, Bestia, Urth Cafe, Zinc Cafe, ATMATEO, Spotify, Stumptown Coffee Roasters, and many new apartments. highlights: Fully Fenced and Secured Site,Multi-Use Space Creative Campus Environment,Close to Studios,Centrally Located with Easy Access to the 134 and I-5 Freeways
propOverview:
The Subject property is located at 4510 Sperry Street, an incomparable setting for a creative work environment, this history-rich 1937 compound is moments from major studios including Disney, ABC, Warner Bros, Paramount and Universal, with views of Griffith Park. Once a WWII aviation school, the campus-like property comprises ±32,190 square feet of multi-use space on over one and a half acres. Streamline Modern architectural style is highlighted with walls of windows, rounded corners, exposed trusses, skylights, covered walkways and exposed brick and concrete construction.
Prime location on the northwest end of Atwater, Golden Road Brewing, a funky industrial venue serving globally inspired pub food and house beers, is around the corner. Downtown Glendale, with the Americana at Brand shopping/dining complex, the Galleria, and an eclectic array of restaurants, is minutes away. The nearby Golden State (5) and Ventura (134) freeway interchange provide convenient access to all of LA.

propOverview:
Welcome to ReadySpaces Los Angeles Downtown, the new home for your business. ReadySpaces is a community of businesses under one roof with private warehouse, storage and office spaces. We offer:
-Private, secure warehouse/storage spaces from 300 to 5,000 SF
-Power (120V, 240V, 208V - varies) and free Wi-Fi in every space
-Access to loading docks and drive-in doors from each space
-Office spaces from 110 to 1,900 SF
-24/7 building access
-Conference rooms, kitchen, and common spaces (free to use)
-Forklifts, pallet jacks, and other equipment (free to use)
-CCTV monitoring and security system
-Flexible lease terms (including short term), ability to grow or shrink your space
-A vibrant community of small businesses
-All-inclusive pricing - no hidden fees or charges
Call us, or schedule a tour today to see all we can offer for your business: https://readyspaces.com/contact-us/

propOverview:
Hard to find Light Industrial/Flex Property located in the heart of Culver City.   The property is great for a variety of light industrial uses including distribution, wholesale, light manufacturing/assembly, warehousing, storage  showroom, studio and other flex uses.  Air Conditioned warehouse area.  Property provides for main boulevard identity/visibility along Jefferson Blvd.  The project provides great parking at 2 spaces/1,000 sf and 12' X 12' ground level loading.  (Landlord will convert the stationery storefront entrance system into a solid or panelized aluminum/glass roll up 12' X 12' loading door).  With the majority of Westside industrial buildings being converted to creative office (or other commercial uses), lease one of the few remaining light industrial/flex spaces in Culver City.  Estimated monthly CAM is .03/sf.    
Culver City is home (or the future home) to some of the most well-known entertainment, technology and media companies including companies like Apple, HBO, Amazon, Sony Pictures, NFL, Smash box Studios, Symantec, National Public Radio, Oracle and more.  These companies are attracted to Culver City based on its central location, access to a talented labor pool, its many surrounding restaurants/retail amenities and finally the vastly improved network of public transportation running through the city, especially via the LA Metro Exposition Line (a 15.2 light rail line that runs between Downtown Los Angeles and Santa Monica).  Culver City is also home to a strong surrounding affluent and educated single family/multi-family residential base, including a multitude of new mixed use developments (multi-unit residential with ground floor retail) either in construction or being planned throughout the City.  With the rapid growth of the Culver City business and residential community, the dining, entertainment and shopping amenities within the City have also grown exponentially to serve this community.  Overall, Culver City is in strong demand and has become a top-tier destination to live, work, play, dine and shop, all while maintaining its historic and small town charm.

propOverview:
DWNTWN Realty Advisors is pleased to present 320-380 NW 26th Street is available for lease. The property consists of two buildings totaling approximately 12,817 SF. There are multiple leasing options for this property with the smallest division containing approximately 4,008 SF in building 2.  Over 150" Feet of frontage along NW 26th Street. Located steps away from Wynwood Walls, arguably the biggest attraction in the area. These retail spaces are ideal for tenants looking to capitalize on prime location, unparalleled exposure and an ever-growing abundance of pedestrian foot traffic. 
Location Description:
The subject property is located on the south side of NW 26th Street, between NW 3rd and 5th Avenues. To the East, The Wynwood Garage, home of WeWork and Punch Bowl Social, To the West, a new mix-used project by Sterling Bay is expected to deliver mid-2020. Additionally, the property is surrounded by a large number of ongoing developments including Wynwood Park, Wynwood Walk, The Moxy Hotel, The Wynwood Hotel, and more. Wynwood is an eclectic district in the urban core of Miami, Florida. It is home to art galleries, retail stores, antique shops, eclectic bars, artisanal eateries and one of the largest open-air street-art installations in the world. Today, Wynwood is recognized globally as a premier destination for art, fashion, innovation, and creative enterprise.

propOverview: 8020 NW 60th Street is located along a dense commercial corridor west of the Miami International Airport. Multiple suppliers, importers, and exporters have selected the area due to the proximity to major transportation routes, plus residential areas with shopping, dining and entertainment options. The Miami International Airport (MIA) is less than 10 miles to the building offering tenants easy access to the country’s largest international cargo airport. PortMiami is the largest passenger port in the world, and one of the largest cargo ports in the United States, and is a short 30-minute drive to the building. The Miami trade route not only serves South Florida's consumption needs but also primarily acts as a bridge between Miami, the Southeast, and the world, which has turned Miami into a significant global trade gateway. In 2014, ownership invested in a new roof, plumbing, electrical, and sprinkler systems for 8020 NW 60th Street. They also updated the office space to include new conference rooms and a renovated kitchen area. Tenants will benefit from the proximity to downtown Miami, major shopping destinations, and the area's many golfing amenities.

highlights: Zoning: T5-O | T3-O
propOverview:
Apex Capital Realty is proud to present the opportunity to lease a freestanding building located in the Midtown neighborhood of Miami. The property features 1,800 SF of office space and over 4,000 SF of flex warehouse
space.
The Midtown Headquarter building features 17" ceilings, 6 street level roll-up garage doors, an oversize paved parking area and plenty of natural light.
This property is located next to the Midtown Miami development which is composed of of retail shops, apartments and an upcoming organic grocer. Currently there are over 2,600 residential units within a mile radius which houses over 7,000 residents.
The property also is blocks of the Wynwood Arts District which is a world recognized tourist destination that receives over 2,000,000 visitors per year. Wynwood is an evolving district that was originally composed of industrial warehouses that were converted into creative office and retail uses. After the rezoning of the district in 2015, Wynwood is now home to a flurry of development that include multiple mid-rise multifamily developments, hotels and office buildings. The property is also blocks away from The Miami Design District which is one of the largest outdoor luxury and design shopping districts.
The Property is easily accessible from Biscayne Blvd. N Miami Ave, I-95 and I-195. The site is also minutes away from Miami International Airport, Miami Beach and Downtown Miami. The site is also blocks away from the proposed Tri-Rail stations on 36 ST and 27th ST which could potential come online in 2020-21 and would connect all of the major tri-county urban areas.

propOverview:
Excellent opportunity to lease 67,000 SF situated on 4.5 acres. This Palmetto Expressway (SR 826) Frontage property is currently being used as Sea Vee Boat’s state-of-the-art manufacturing facility. The Property features a warehouse manufacturing facility inclusive of 11,500 SF of office space on two floors. The property also offers street level loading with over-sized doors and truck wells, on city water and sewer, outside well-field, fully fire sprinklered, 20’ ceiling height, twin tee roof, 60 parking spaces, and heavy three phase power. The 4.5 acre lot makes it ideal for users requiring extensive parking for trucks, cars or outside storage. In addition, the IU-3 zoning is the highest and heaviest industrial classification available in Miami-Dade County.
Located on the Frontage Road West of the Palmetto Expressway between NW 58th St and NW 74th St offers a very strategic location. The current traffic count of 238,000 vehicles per day is one of the highest in the state providing companies unsurpassed exposure to their brand name. NW 58th St or NW 74th St entry/exit ramps to the Palmetto Expressway make connecting to Okeechobee Rd (US 27), SR I-75 and Florida Turnpike an ease for trucking access and located less than 2.5 miles from Miami International Airport and 9.5 miles from the Port of Miami.

propOverview: Chariff Realty Group is proud to present for lease: 3701 NW 3 Ave, located at the hard corner of NW 3rd Avenue and 37th Street in Midtown Miami. This five-story 20,000 SF building, with an expected delivery date of First Quarter 2019, is optimally located just blocks away from the Wynwood Arts District, the Design District, and the MiMo Historical District. In addition to its prime location, 3701 NW 3 Ave will have the convenience of a café and a parking garage on the first floor. Midtown has remained one of the more ideally priced locations among its neighborhood. With close proximity to the cluster of fashion and design stores of the Design District, and the multitude of visitors, both foreign and local, to the streets of Wynwood, Midtown has managed to maintain its own distinction as a significantly popular dining and shopping venue in Miami, as well as a buzzing residential habitat. Midtown is also the location of the annual Art Miami and Concept fairs, one of the top Art Basel Miami satellite spots. 3701 NW 3 Ave is the perfect location for tenants such as luxury furniture showrooms, galleries, interior design offices, textiles and flooring showrooms, etc. The building offers ample on-site parking, a café, and great co-tenancy, with the multitude of year-round visitors, consistent high traffic, and unparalleled location in Miami’s most popular neighborhood, 3701 NW 3 Ave is sure to be a focal point for design oriented retail.

propOverview:
Great opportunity to reposition as retail/office, taking advantage of the property' s proximity to Downtown Doral and its rapidly evolving neighborhood. Strategically located in th heart of Doral, one of  the fastest growing markets in the nation, this corner property enjoys unparalleled access to all major expressway arteries and public transportation. Its location is just minutes away from Miami International Airport (MIA). Adjacent to the City of Doral' s Government Center, Provident Doral at the Blue and in close proximity to Trump National Doral. This facility offers a variety of spaces, ample offices, secure parking and access from both 54th Street and 84th Avenue.
5400 NW 84th Avenue is located in Doral, one of the fastest growing markets in the nation. This property is directly adjacent to the city' s Government Center and the Downtown Doral office park. The heart of the city is the growing metropolis of Downtown Doral, a true live, work, play & learn community with over 2,800 residential units, around 1 million square feet of offices, 180,000 square feet of retail, and a state-of-the-art charter school. The property enjoys superior access to all major expressway arteries and public transportation. It is also just minutes away from Miami International Airport and adjacent to Trump National Doral Golf Club & Provident Doral at the Blue.

propOverview:
Welcome to ReadySpaces Houston, the new home for your business. ReadySpaces is a community of businesses under one roof with individual warehouse, storage and office spaces. We offer:
-Private, secure warehouse/storage spaces from 250 to 5,000 SF
-Power (120V, 240V, 208V - varies) and free Wi-Fi in every space
-Access to loading docks and drive-in doors from each space
-Office spaces from 110 to 300 SF
-24/7 building access
-Conference rooms, kitchen, and common spaces (free to use)
-Forklifts, pallet jacks, and other equipment (free to use)
-CCTV monitoring and security system
-Flexible lease terms (including short term), ability to grow or shrink your space
-A vibrant community of small businesses
-All-inclusive pricing - no hidden fees or charges
Property has great access to I-45, downtown Houston, and University of Houston.
BROKERS: No fuss. Just make a call and receive a market commission if your client signs a lease. You don't have to show up - we'll handle the tour.

hoodMarket: The Northern Chicago area includes some of Chicago’s most historic and desirable neighborhoods, such as Lakeview, Edgewater, Uptown and Lincoln Park. The western portion of this corridor was historically zoned exclusively for manufacturing, but changes in Chicago’s zoning policy opened much of this land to multifamily and office uses. The result is a mix of housing, office, and industrial uses within this diverse and dynamic area of Chicago. The eastern portion of the area boasts one of the highest population densities in the Chicago region, while the western portion includes most of the area’s manufacturing and warehouse stock. ,Manufacturers and logistics companies are drawn to this area in part due to its accessibility, with its well-connected network of interstates providing access to over 10 million people and one of the nation’s busiest ports. The area’s small and mid-sized manufacturing companies benefit from the area’s dense, infill location and span across a variety of industries, including durable and non-durable goods wholesaling, commercial printing, HVAC, plumbing, and construction, ,Millions of square feet of industrial space have been demolished in North Chicago over the past decade, as many industrial owners capitalized on quickly rising land values by selling to multifamily and office developers. The decline in available space, coupled with steady tenant demand, pushed vacancy to near historic lows. In recognition of Chicago’s growing manufacturing activity, together with the area’s appealing last-mile distribution location, North Chicago is expected to continue to attract both large and small industrial tenants.
propOverview: Nestled on the border of Galewood and Belmont-Cragin in Northwest Side Chicago, Austin 1900 Building offers flexibility for almost any business and a location easy to reach for commuters. 5 minutes from W North Avenue, drivers can reach destinations like River North or O’Hare International Airport in around 30 minutes, traffic permitting. There is ample parking on-site for those commuting by car, but Austin 1900 Building also offers superb connectivity to public transit. The Galewood Metra Station is a 10-minute walk from the building and services the Milwaukee District West train line, which takes riders east to Union Station in around 40 minutes or as far west as Big Timber, past Elgin, in around 72. Buses on route 86 run along Narragansett Avenue and route 91 is on N Austin Avenue. The property stretches between these two major roads, making it easy to reach either. Across from the building is Amundsen Park, which has a new track and field providing recreation options to employees. Brickyard Mall is the premier retail destination in the area and only a 5-minute drive from the building. The center is home to grocery, fitness, and plenty of shopping and dining options from notable brands. Austin 1900 Building itself consists of three parcels. The first is 1900 N Austin Ave, an approximately 700,000 square foot office, research and development, and warehouse building. The second two parcels are both vacant land sites to either side of the building, approximately 6 acres to the west and 10 to the east. The offices on the south and east side offer breathtaking views of Amundsen Park and beyond to the Chicago skyline. The interior features a modern lobby, and flexibility between open offices, event spaces, space for research and development, and warehouse units with loading docks and drive-in doors. Energy-efficient improvements are in place, including the installation of LED lighting and a solar array that has been running since 2011.

highlights: Both units offer a great corporate image and location in LA's northernmost neighborhood, featuring easy access to nearby freeways and modern finishes.,15148 Bledsoe St features 4 docks, 3 drive-in doors, up to 18' clear height, and 1000 amps of 480 volt power.,13077 Bradley Ave features 1 dock, 1 drive-in door, and up to 15' clear height.,Located just 5 minutes from the 5 and 210 freeways and 10 minutes to the 118,405, and 14 freeways.,The office space in Bledsoe features private offices overlooking the warehouse area, a conference room, and floor-to-ceiling glass partitions.,The Sylmar Towne Shopping Center provides numerous dining, shopping, and conveniences options for employees in a 6-minute drive from the property.
hoodMarket: Sylmar is the northernmost neighborhood in the sprawling City of Los Angeles. Its distance from the area’s premiere employment and residential hubs give the area a suburban feel, but interstates 5, 405, and 210, collectively some of Los Angeles’ most heavily traveled highways, converge here. Interstate 5 is California’s main north-south artery and continues on into the Central Valley, while Interstate 210 offers direct access to the Inland Empire’s vast industrial landscape.,Manufacturing has been a staple of the area since the 1970s, with companies like L-3 Ocean Systems, Abbot/St. Jude Medical, and PPG Aerospace maintaining significant manufacturing operations here. While overall manufacturing employment has been declining in Los Angeles for decades, the growth of the logistics sector has helped offset those losses. ,The area’s strategic location at the conjunction of several major highways helps underpin strong demand for industrial space. New industrial development is minimal though, a common refrain across Los Angeles County.
propOverview: Located in Los Angeles’s northernmost neighborhood, 15148 Bledsoe Street in Sylmar, California, provides an excellent corporate image and location. Initially constructed in 1969, the entire building was renovated in 2015, and Unit B features office space with modern finishes and all the industrial amenities necessary for today’s industrial businesses. The 3,767 square-foot office overlooks the warehouse area and features offices and a conference room with attractive floor-to-ceiling glass partitions. The warehouse area features clear heights ranging from 14’-18’, 4 (four) covered truck well loading positions and 3 (three) ground level doors, and 1000-amps of 480-volt, 3-phase, 4-wire power throughout. The property provides multiple, convenient distribution options with only a 5-minute drive to the 5 and 210 freeways and a 10-minute drive to the 118, 405, and 14 freeways. The Bob Hope Airport can be reached in an 18-minute drive and the Los Angeles International Airport is just 35 minutes away, the Port of Long Beach is only 40 miles away, and the UP- Los Angeles rail line is only 21.6 miles from the property. For employees, the Sylmar/San Fernando Commuter Rail (Antelope Valley Line) is a 6-minute drive away, and the property is surrounded by densely packed residential neighborhoods. For shopping, dining, and conveniences, the Sylmar Towne Shopping Center is 6 minutes away and is surrounded by the bustling commercial district at the intersection of Hubbard Street and Glenoaks Boulevard.

propOverview: 1388 Daisy Avenue offers turnkey solutions for delivery-only business models, dramatically cutting real estate and labor costs. These “plug-and-play” spaces start at 200 square feet and come equipped with brand new gas and plumbing connections, floor drains, sinks, hoods, Ansul systems, and cold and dry storage space. Additionally, these spaces feature health permits - all that is needed to start a business is an idea and creativity. This Long Beach address is in a prime spot to provide dining options to the surrounding population, located just two miles from the beach and blocks from Seaside Park. The city of Long Beach celebrates its diverse community with an eclectic roster of cultural festivals, and the coastline is also an immensely popular tourist destination. This year-round influx of consumers paired with Long Beach’s reputation for being exceptionally bicycle-friendly provides convenient access and plenty of potential business. In the immediate area, residents within a 1-mile radius of 1388 Daisy contributed to a consumer spending total of $412 million, with over $135 million spent on food and alcohol.

Light filled space with 14’ ceilings and west-facing window wall featuring:
	•	5-7 generous work stations in open office layout (landlord is open to some modifications for the right tenant)
	•	generous built-in storage at each desk, plus cabinets, flat files and shelves in designated storage areas
	•	printer / plotter / copier area (shared use included in lease)
	•	conference room (comfortably seats 8 people) with 72” screen w/ videoconference setup, all-round pin-up walls for presentations and meetings
	•	extensive architectural reference library of books, magazine subscriptions, catalogues and material samples
	•	Fully stocked kitchenette w/ espresso/coffee, filtered cold / hot water, refrigerator, sink
	•	Parking: 3 shared spaces in office lot. Guest/client parking in front of building. Good surface parking available within 1 block
	•	in walking distance to a wide selection of lunch spots, retail, grocery stores, gyms, entertainment and other amenities, Santa Monica's 3rd Street Promenade, and 4th or 17th Street METRO stations.  
	•	3 blocks from Lincoln Blvd. HWY 10 onramp
Rent includes:
	•	DEDICATED DESK + SHARED AREAS AS DESCRIBED ABOVE
	•	SECURITY / ALARM COMPANY
	•	UTILITIES (ELECTRICITY, WATER, TRASH, RECYCLING) 
	•	FIOS INTERNET
	•	WEEKLY CLEANING
	•	KITCHEN SUPPLIES, COFFEE, FILTERED WATER
	
	•	SHARED OFFICE EQUIPMENT:
	•	LASER PRINTER / COPIER / FAX, 42” PLOTTER, 
	•	BINDING MACHINE, LIGHT TABLE, CUTTING STATION

Optional extras:
Dedicated Phone Extension(s) 	  30 $ /month ea.
